===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|inflatio|īnflātiō|expansion", "blowing up|lang=la}}, from {{term|inflatus|īnflātus|lang=la}}, the perfect passive participle of {{term|inflo|īnflō|blow into", "expand}}, from {{term|in||into|lang=la}} + {{term|flo|flō|blow|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{rhymes|eɪʃən}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An act, instance of, or state of expansion or increase in size, especially by injection of a gas.
#: ''The '''inflation''' of the balloon took five hours.''
# {{economics}} An increase in the general level of prices or in the [[cost of living]].
# {{economics}} A decline in the value of [[money]].
# {{economics}} An increase in the quantity of [[money]], leading to a devaluation of existing money.
# Undue expansion or increase, as of academic grades.
# {{context|cosmology}} An extremely rapid expansion of the universe, theorised to have occurred very shortly after the [[big bang]].

